10:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Krisp is best suited for remote workers on calls, noisy environment meetings, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Suno, meanwhile, shines for creating music without instruments, content creators needing custom music, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2017, Krisp describes itself as \"AI noise cancellation for calls and meetings.\" Suno, established in 2023, positions itself as \"Create full songs with AI from a text prompt.\" With 6 years between them, Krisp brings the maturity and proven track record of a veteran platform, while Suno offers the fresh perspective and modern architecture of a newer entrant."}]]}]
11:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Krisp** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to more features (3 vs 2), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Suno is a poor choice — far from it. Suno excels in its own right, particularly for creating music without instruments and content creators needing custom music.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value best-in-class noise cancellation, go with Krisp. If incredibly easy to use matters more to you, Suno is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
